ACTRESS  Grace Agbo has shared how she manages heartbreak. In an exclusive chat with The Nation, Agbo stated that she usually give herself little time to heal before moving on with her life. Giving details on her kind of man, she said, “I am not particular about the physical appearance of a man. A good man is okay for me. I just want a really good man inside. A man that has the fear of God and pays attention to me.”   King Promise thrills at Trace Live     Sir Adegoke Ogunwusi, Dele Gold, others embark on US, Canada…     Obi Cubana grateful to God at 47   Agbo also dismissed claims that Nollywood contributed to the rise in money ritual killings. The actress stressed that Nigerian movies actually  curbed money ritual killings by showing the dangers associated with engaging in money rituals and advantages of not engaging in money rituals. Speaking in an interview to mark her birthday, Agbo, who is also a firefighter, said she would stay indoors to celebrate her birthday to enable her to reflect on her life. She said some widows and under privileged children have been earmarked to get a token from her as she celebrates.